# HomericIntelligence main Branch Protection: The Two-Layer Split

## Overview

| Field | Value |
| ------- | ------- |
| **Date** | 2026-05-31 |
| **Objective** | Document the intentional two-layer (ruleset + classic) protection design on HI `main` and the gh-api gotchas encountered while auditing/applying it across all 15 repos |
| **Outcome** | Successful — both layers audited and applied live via `gh api` on all 15 HomericIntelligence repos; design and constraints confirmed |
| **Verification** | verified-ci (applied + verified live via gh api on all 15 HI repos, 2026-05-31) |

## When to Use

- You are managing HomericIntelligence `main`-branch protection and need to know where a given rule lives
- You must decide whether a new rule belongs in a **repo ruleset** vs **classic branch protection**
- A PR is `BLOCKED` by a review or status check that the **ruleset** reports as `0`/absent — the OTHER layer (classic) is adding it
- A ruleset PUT returns `HTTP 422: data matches no possible input` when you add `required_conversation_resolution`
- `gh api repos/<O>/<R>/branches/main/protection` returns a 404 body and you risk parsing its keys as fake required-check contexts
- You see fully-signed PRs with empty `reviewDecision` that still will not merge

Related: [[ci-cd-ruleset-bootstrap-deadlock]], [[ci-cd-homeric-intelligence-merge-gotchas]], [[git-gpg-sign-email-mismatch-silent-unsigned-blocks-merge]].

## Verified Workflow

(See v1.0.0 .md — full two-layer audit/apply workflow: audit both layers, compute EXTRAS as set difference, full-replace ruleset PUT, set classic = extras + conversation-resolution only, 404 guard, independent classic-reviews audit.)

## Failed Attempts

| Attempt | What Was Tried | Why It Failed | Lesson Learned |
| --------- | ---------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| Attempt 1 | Added `{"type":"required_conversation_resolution"}` to a repo ruleset and PUT it | HTTP 422 — not a valid ruleset rule type | `required_conversation_resolution` is classic-only |
| Attempt 2 | PUT the ruleset with just the two new rules | Ruleset PUT REPLACES the entire `.rules` array | Ruleset edits are NOT additive — fetch, dedup, append, PUT full object |
| Attempt 3 | Parsed `branches/main/protection` 404 body for ProjectKeystone | 404 body keys became fake required contexts | Guard for `.status == "404"` before extracting contexts |
| Attempt 4 | Assumed ruleset `required_approving_review_count=0` meant no review gate anywhere | ProjectNestor CLASSIC required 1 review, blocking ~18 signed PRs | Audit BOTH layers; the union wins |

